      "message": "I like this. It also ties in with another change I\u0027d like to make: Easier testing for fragmentProcessor types (which is a special case that\u0027s tested in many places). I think that fp is the *only* kOther type now (or sk_Caps might be, too?). In any case, I have some ideas about making the runtime-effect version of fp actually called \"shader\" (and not be an alias to fragmentProcessor). And there\u0027s a chance we want two \"callable skia\" types in runtime effects (shader vs. color_filter).\n\nSo, how about we add another type-kind for \"SkiaCallable\" (better name?) that is currently just fragmentProcessor, and then we can update the various tests for fFragmentProcessor (or places that even do `name \u003d\u003d \"fragmentProcessor\"`).",
